servings: 2
course: main course
---

1 packet chicken breast strips
1 sachet Southeast Asian Spice Blend
1 bag red cabbage
1 packet flat noodles
½ lemon
½ fresh chilli
1 packet Asian Stir-Fry Mix
1 packet oyster sauce
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 bunch coriander
drizzle Olive Oil

Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat.
Cook chicken strips and spice blend, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 3 mins.
Add cabbage and cook, tossing, until softened, 1 min.

Meanwhile, pierce noodle packet and microwave until hot and steaming, 2 mins.
Halve lemon. Slice chilli (if using).

Add stir fry mix to the pan and toss through until wilted and tender, 2 mins.
Remove pan from the heat, add noodles, oyster sauce, peanuts and a good squeeze of lemon juice.
Toss to coat.
Plate up noodles and garnish with crispy shallots and chilli (if using).
Tear over coriander.